  "poem": {
    "content": "The air turned brisk, a forest's breath,\nas a couple strolled, near insane with grief.\nHe winked, a gesture shadowed by the trees,\nshe tilted her head, beyond relief.\n\nA vendor stood, by a road ahead,\nhis cart piled high, her grocery need.\nShe thought about escape, about a plunge\ninto depths where silent sorrows bleed.\n\nBut sunshine, warm, upon her face,\na jewel-like promise, caught in a blur.\nA moment held, in fragile lace,\nrenew the hope, the insane thoughts deter.\n\nHe took her hand, a silent vow,\nto stand with her, here and now.\nThe forest whispers, soft and deep,\nwhile through the trees their secrets creep.\nThe grocery bag, a weight they bore,\nthey walk ahead, and nothing more.",
